PEOPLE v. SQUIRES. (Supreme Court, Appellate Division, Fourth Department. December 6, 1905.) Appeal from Special Term. George Squires was prosecuted for a violation of the liquor tax law. Erom a judgment sustaining his demurrer to the indictment, the people cipjp6cil ¡Reversed

Argued before McLENNAN, P. J., and SPRING, WILLIAMS, HISCOCK, and NASH, JJ.

PER CURIAM.

Interlocutory judgment reversed, and demurrer overruled, with leave to defendant to plead to the indictment, on opinion! of Nash, J., in People v. Myers (decided at the present term of this court) 95 N. Y. Supp. 993.
